### Multi-turn chat: same session, two gateway calls
# Replace YOUR_COSTKATANA_KEY and YOUR_PROJECT_ID.
#
# Pattern:
# 1) First POST: messages = [ { role: user, content: "..." } ]
# 2) Second POST: messages = [ user1, assistant1, user2 ]  (full thread)
#
# The model needs the full array each time. On costkatana-backend-nest, Usage rows
# default to one turn: Request + stored input tokens use the latest user message
# when 2+ messages are present (full body still proxied upstream).
#
# If your gateway infers the provider, you can omit CostKatana-Target-Url (see 2-gateway README).

@baseUrl = https://api.costkatana.com/api/gateway
@ckKey = YOUR_COSTKATANA_KEY
@projectId = YOUR_PROJECT_ID

### Turn 1 — single user message
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/chat/completions
CostKatana-Auth: Bearer {{ckKey}}
CostKatana-Target-Url: https://api.openai.com
CostKatana-Project-Id: {{projectId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Say hello in exactly five words." }
  ]
}

### Turn 2 — include assistant reply from turn 1, then the new user line
# Paste the assistant message.content from the previous response into the placeholder below.

POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/chat/completions
CostKatana-Auth: Bearer {{ckKey}}
CostKatana-Target-Url: https://api.openai.com
CostKatana-Project-Id: {{projectId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "Say hello in exactly five words." },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "REPLACE_WITH_ASSISTANT_TEXT_FROM_TURN_1" },
    { "role": "user", "content": "Now reply with a six-word follow-up question." }
  ]
}

###
# ✅ OpenAI: /v1/chat/completions + chat models (gpt-4o-mini, gpt-4o, …)
# ✅ Anthropic: /v1/messages + Claude model ids + max_tokens (see basic-routing.http)
# ❌ Do not use a Claude model id on chat/completions or a GPT id on /v1/messages
